  "title": "Medical Affairs Assistant Manager [West]",
  "description": "<p><strong>[Job ID: 1175193]</strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Organize and provide secretariat support for clinical quality assurance committees, workgroups, and meetings.</li><li>Collaborate with stakeholders on quality assurance, patient safety, continual improvement, and risk management initiatives.</li><li>Plan, develop, and implement quality improvement projects.</li><li>Prepare reports and conduct data analysis for clinical governance functions.</li><li>Act as a resource person and maintain positive relationships with medical, allied health, and administrative teams.</li><li>Support hospital licensing, internal audits, incident management, and clinical quality records review programs.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Bachelor’s degree in a relevant discipline is required.</strong></li><li><strong>Minimum 3 years of healthcare experience.</strong></li><li>Experience in healthcare administration, clinical quality (e.g., JCI, LEAN, Six Sigma, Root Cause Analysis, PDCA), and/or risk management is an added advantage.</li><li>Experience in medico-legal matters or quality assurance is an added advantage.</li><li>Proficient in MS Office applications (Word, Excel, PowerPoint).</li><li>Meticulous with strong problem-solving, interpersonal, oral, and written communication skills.</li></ul><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. However, rest assured that all applications will be updated to our resume bank for future opportunities.</p><p>Please kindly refer to the Privacy Policy of Good Job Creations for your reference: https://goodjobcreations.com.sg/en/privacy-policy/</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Felicia Chiam Kar Min<br />EA Personnel Reg. No.: R25152370<br />EA Licence No.: 07C5771 </p>",
